{
  "text": "In our study, the bioassays showed a significantly increase in CL50 in chlorinated water but there are not visible reduction of Cry and Cyt toxins by treatment with chlorine in SDS-PAGE analysis. Chlorine is a non-selective oxidant with a number of effects over the living systems: reacts with a variety of cellular components [CITATION_1] , deactivates enzymatic active sites, decreases the biological functions of proteins and produces deleterious effects on DNA [CITATION_2] . In addition chlorinated waters affect the permeability of the cytoplasmic membrane [CITATION_3] , which could lead to cell death and inhibit the growth of B. thuringiensis [CITATION_4] .",
  "correct_citation": {
